.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINYEARMONTH.ADD" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainYearMonth.add \- Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.add()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]add()\f[B]\f[R] method of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] instances returns a new
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] object representing this year\-month
moved forward by a given duration (in a form convertible by
\f[CR]Temporal.Duration.from()\f[R]).
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
add(duration)
add(duration, options)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]duration\f[R]
A string, an object, or a \f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] instance
representing a duration to add to this year\-month.
It is converted to a \f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] object using the same
algorithm as \f[CR]Temporal.Duration.from()\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]options\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An object containing the following property:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]overflow\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A string specifying the behavior when a date component is out of range.
Possible values are:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]\(dqconstrain\(dq\f[R] (default)
The date component is clamped to the valid range.
.TP
\f[B]\(dqreject\(dq\f[R]
A \f[CR]RangeError\f[R] is thrown if the date component is out of range.
.RE
.RE
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] object representing the
year\-month specified by the original \f[CR]PlainYearMonth\f[R], plus
the duration.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]RangeError\f[R]
Thrown if the result is not in the representable range, which is
±(10\(ha8 + 1) days, or about ±273,972.6 years, from the Unix epoch.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f[CR]duration\f[R] is handled in this way:
.IP \(bu 2
Move forward by the number of years, keeping the \f[CR]monthCode\f[R]
the same.
If the \f[CR]monthCode\f[R] is invalid in the resulting year (impossible
for Gregorian and ISO 8601, but possible for calendars with leap
months), we adjust based on the \f[CR]overflow\f[R] option: for
\f[CR]constrain\f[R], we pick another month according to the cultural
conventions of that calendar\(cqs users.
For example, because the leap month is usually thought of as a duplicate
of another month, we may pick the month that it is a duplicate of.
.IP \(bu 2
Move forward by the number of months, adjusting the year if necessary.
.IP \(bu 2
For all units smaller than \f[CR]months\f[R] (weeks, days, hours,
minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds), they are
converted to the number of days.
All commonly supported calendars use fixed\-length weeks, so the number
of weeks is just converted to the number of days.
If the rule is more complex, we may take an approach similar to shifting
months.
Then, we move forward by that number of days, starting on the first day
of the month, adjusting the month and year if necessary.
Durations smaller than the current month\(cqs length therefore have no
effect.
.PP
The internal reference day is then chosen to be the first valid day of
the month, irrespective of the original reference day or the number of
days in the duration.
For the Gregorian calendar, overflow cannot happen because every year
always has 12 months, and any increment less than a month is just
ignored.
.PP
Adding a duration is equivalent to subtracting its negation.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Adding a duration in ISO 8601 calendar
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] start = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from(\(dq2021\-01\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] end = start.add({ years: 1, months: 2, weeks: 3, days: 4 });
console.log(end.toString()); \f[I]// 2022\-03\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] end2 = start.add({ years: \-1, months: \-2, weeks: \-3, days: \-4 });
console.log(end2.toString()); \f[I]// 2019\-11\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] distance = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from(\(dq2020\-01\(dq).until(\(dq2021\-01\(dq); \f[I]// 366 days\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] end3 = start.add(distance);
console.log(end3.toString()); \f[I]// 2022\-01\f[R]
.EE
.SS Adding a duration in a non\-ISO calendar
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] start = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from(\(dq2021\-02\-01[u\-ca=chinese]\(dq);
console.log(start.toLocaleString(\(dqen\-US\(dq, { calendar: \(dqchinese\(dq })); \f[I]// 11/2020\f[R]
console.log(start.toString()); \f[I]// 2021\-01\-13[u\-ca=chinese]\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] end = start.add({ months: 1 });
console.log(end.toLocaleString(\(dqen\-US\(dq, { calendar: \(dqchinese\(dq })); \f[I]// 12/2020\f[R]
console.log(end.toString()); \f[I]// 2021\-02\-12[u\-ca=chinese]\f[R]

\f[I]// Adding an extra day has no effect at all\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] end2 = start.add({ months: 1, days: 1 });
console.log(end2.toLocaleString(\(dqen\-US\(dq, { calendar: \(dqchinese\(dq })); \f[I]// 12/2020\f[R]
\f[I]// The reference day doesn\(aqt change, because it\(aqs always the first day of the Chinese month\f[R]
console.log(end2.toString()); \f[I]// 2021\-02\-12[u\-ca=chinese]\f[R]

\f[I]// Start in a leap month\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] start2 = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from({
  year: 5730,
  monthCode: \(dqM05L\(dq,
  calendar: \(dqhebrew\(dq,
});
console.log(start2.toLocaleString(\(dqen\-US\(dq, { calendar: \(dqhebrew\(dq })); \f[I]// Adar I 5730\f[R]
\f[I]// End in another leap month\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] end3 = start2.add({ years: 3 });
console.log(end3.toLocaleString(\(dqen\-US\(dq, { calendar: \(dqhebrew\(dq })); \f[I]// Adar I 5733\f[R]
.EE
.SS Adding a duration with overflow
If we move a few years and the corresponding month is invalid in this
year, then we adjust the month based on the \f[CR]overflow\f[R] option.
.IP
.EX
\f[I]// Start in a leap month\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] start = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from({
  year: 5730,
  monthCode: \(dqM05L\(dq,
  calendar: \(dqhebrew\(dq,
});
\f[I]// Hebrew leap years occur every 2 or 3 years, and 5731 is not a leap year\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] end = start.add({ years: 1 });
console.log(end.toLocaleString(\(dqen\-US\(dq, { calendar: \(dqhebrew\(dq })); \f[I]// Adar 5731\f[R]
console.log(end.monthCode); \f[I]// M06\f[R]
console.log(end.toString()); \f[I]// 1971\-02\-26[u\-ca=hebrew]\f[R]

\f[I]// Any further month additions are based on the clamped year\-month\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] end2 = start.add({ years: 1, months: 2 });
console.log(end2.monthCode); \f[I]// M08\f[R]
console.log(end2.toString()); \f[I]// 1971\-04\-26[u\-ca=hebrew]\f[R]

\f[I]// Compare with the same addition in a different order that results in no overflow:\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] end3 = start.add({ months: 2 }).add({ years: 1 });
console.log(end3.monthCode); \f[I]// M07\f[R]
console.log(end3.toString()); \f[I]// 1971\-03\-27[u\-ca=hebrew]\f[R]
.EE
.PP
Note that the following is not an overflow because the year can just
increment:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] start = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from(\(dq2021\-01\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] end = start.add({ months: 100 });
console.log(end.toString()); \f[I]// 2029\-05\f[R]
.EE
.PP
You can also throw an error if the date component is out of range:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] start = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from({
  year: 5730,
  monthCode: \(dqM05L\(dq,
  calendar: \(dqhebrew\(dq,
});
\f[B]const\f[R] end = start.add({ years: 1 }, { overflow: \(dqreject\(dq }); \f[I]// RangeError: invalid \(dqmonthCode\(dq calendar field: M05L\f[R]
.EE
